org.jconfigurations.configurators

Class CollectionConfigurator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jconfigurations.configurators.BaseConfigurator
      • org.jconfigurations.configurators.CollectionConfigurator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configurator

    public class CollectionConfigurator
extends BaseConfigurator
    The CollectionConfigurator will target all CollectionConfiguration fields of an object. Unless specified otherwise, the CollectionConfigurator will use the DefaultCollectionTypeConverterFunction to convert configuration values into instances of the appropriate types before assigning them to fields.
    Author:
    George Aristy
    See Also:
    CollectionFieldConverterFunction, DefaultCollectionTypeConverterFunction

        public CollectionConfigurator(ConfigurationSource source,
                              Configurator configurator,
                              ErrorFunction<Field,String> fieldNameFunction,
                              ErrorFunction<Field,CollectionConfigurationConverter> fieldConverterFunction)
        Fully customizable constructor that allows the user to chain link another configurator in order to compose a multi-featured chain.
        Parameters:
        source - the ConfigurationSource that provides the configurations
        configurator - another Configurator to which this instance will hand off the target object to once this CollectionConfigurator has finished configuring the object.
        fieldNameFunction - the function used to produce the field's name (see Name).
        fieldConverterFunction - the function used to produce an instance of the appropriate converter for a given field.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any of the inputs is null.
